// https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/ῥέα https://logeion.uchicago.edu/ῥέα
// Alternative form of ῥεῖα (rheîa)
// ---Cunliffe---
// ῥέα, ῥεῖα (Ϝρέα, Ϝρεῖα) (ῥέα in Iliad only. A
//    monosyllable in  ).
// 1. Easily, with ease, without effort or difficulty,
//    readily: ῥέα πάλλεν  ὅπως ἵπποι ῥεῖα διέλθοιεν
//    (without giving the driver trouble, without shying)
//    (with
//    effortless stride), 144 (without check),
//    (nimbly),  (smoothly),  (without
//    check, straight),  etc.:  (without more
//    ado),  (you
//    saw it at once), 305,
// 2. At ease, at one's ease: θεοὶ ῥεῖα ζώοντες :
// 3. Without thinking of the consequences, lightly,
//    readily: ἄλλον κεν θεῶν ῥεῖα κατευνήσαιμι --
//    Sim.: τούτοισι ταῦτα μέλει ῥεῖα (they enjoy
//    themselves with no thought for the morrow)

{
  "word":"ῥέα",
  "medium":"easily",
  "syn":"ῥεῖα"
